## Sqaure Brackets []

You create a List using square brackets `[]` and separating the items with commas.

```dart
// A List containing 3 Strings
List<String> heroes = ['Batman', 'Superman', 'Flash'];

// A List containing ints
List<int> luckyNumbers = [7, 13, 42];
```
Notice the `<String>` tag? That tells Dart EXACTLY what this List is allowed to hold.

slides.codeSnippet:
void main() {
  List<String> inventory = ['Sword', 'Shield', 'Potion'];

  // Add an item to the end!
  inventory.add('Bow');

  // Remove an item entirely!
  inventory.remove('Shield');

  print(inventory);
}
